was so focused on getting into graduate school

00:41:36.240 --> 00:41:40.390
that the goal of those four years was how
do you get all A's?

00:41:40.390 --> 00:41:43.970
The easiest way to get all A's is to take
the easiest courses.

00:41:43.970 --> 00:41:47.300
So I worked with the athletic department and
helped their athletes, and in exchange, I

00:41:47.300 --> 00:41:55.460
got to take the classes that were set aside
for them, which instant A. But I never took

00:41:55.460 --> 00:41:59.080
the classes of what I wanted to learn, and
what would've challenged me, and what would've

00:41:59.080 --> 00:42:00.080
grown.

00:42:00.080 --> 00:42:03.360
So took that approach, and I'll embarrass
one of my sons went to Brown.

00:42:03.360 --> 00:42:08.030
When he came to me and said, "Brown has no
required courses and no grades."

00:42:08.030 --> 00:42:11.390
I'm going like, I thought of myself, I go,
"Oh, four years of partying."

00:42:11.390 --> 00:42:14.630
Then I looked at it, and it's a market economy.

00:42:14.630 --> 00:42:16.030
Think of it for a second.

00:42:16.030 --> 00:42:18.980
The English department only gets funded if
kids take the English courses.

00:42:18.980 --> 00:42:21.750
Geology only gets funded ... No one's required
to take any of them.

00:42:21.750 --> 00:42:26.080
So you're only going to take the classes,
and there's no grade, so no risk, that you

00:42:26.080 --> 00:42:30.170
hear are the most stimulated, most interesting,
greatest classes.

00:42:30.170 --> 00:42:33.340
So all the course and the quality of those
courses go up.

00:42:33.340 --> 00:42:39.560
As opposed to me taking rocks for jocks or
whatever simplistic thing that the person

00:42:39.560 --> 00:42:44.950
teaching it hated teaching it, and the students
hated taking it, but it was just a tick box.

00:42:44.950 --> 00:42:50.500
If you can get out of that tick box mentality
... So Brown's completely changed the dynamic

00:42:50.500 --> 00:42:55.760
and made it a buyer's markets where students
are the ones deciding which professors keep

00:42:55.760 --> 00:43:00.010
a job because if nobody takes the class, it's
over.

00:43:00.010 --> 00:43:03.710
